doc.field: U.S. Government Building and portion of south west colonnade. Crowd seated on steps. Lagoon with docked boats.
Arch of States looking north. Administration Arch visible through archway.

View across lagoon of Grand Court, looking southwest toward Mines and Mining, Liberal Arts, Fine Arts, Building, balustraded island, and U.S. Government Building. Swan boat and gondolas docked. Benches and electric light columns in foreground.

East end of lagoon. Gondola and Swan boat docked in water. Planter in foreground. Machinery and Electricity Building to the north. Rinehart Studio and Grand Colonnade to the east. A few spectators descending the staircase to lagoon.

View of grand court, looking northwest. Machinery and Electricity and Manufacturers Buildings, Administration Arch, Agriculture Building, balustraded island, and U.S. Government Building to the West. Spectators walking in foreground.
Mines and Mining Building and colonnade. East end of lagoon with garden and benches visible. Crowd walking.
Section of Manufactures Building with Colonnade.
View of Machinery and Electricity Building from across lagoon. Grand Colonnade and Moorish Palace visible in distance to the east.
Grand Colonnade. Auditorium visible in background. Gondola docked in lagoon. Staircase leading to lagoon. Small portion of Mines and Mining Building visible to the south.
Machinery and Electricity Building, looking northwest. Stairs leading to lagoon, with gondolas docked. Benches and light crowd, seated and walking, in foreground.
East end of lagoon, looking south. Auditorium visible beyond tiered gardens and Grand Colonnade. Mines and Mining Building visible to the west. Three blurred spectators in foreground.
View across lagoon looking south toward Fine Arts Building and balustraded island.

View across lagoon toward staircase leading up to grand court. Gondola docked in water. Grand Colonnade with roofline of Moorish Palace visible. Corner of Machinery and Electricity Building visible to the west.
Twin Tower Restaurant and Grand Colonnade
twin tower restaurant and grand colonnade
Girls and Boys Building with signage for The Home Restaurant. Twin Tower Restaurant, and Grand Colonnade, looking northeast. Light crowd walking. Concession stand to the east.
Balustraded Island with garden and planter, looking northeast toward Manufacturers Building. Machinery and Electricity Building, Twin Tower Restaurants, and Grand Colonnade visible in background.
Mines and Mining Building, looking west. Liberal Arts, Fine Arts, and U.S. Government Buildings in background. Fire hydrant in foreground.

Bemis Brothers Bag Company Building, looking northwest. Signage reads "Bemis, Boston, St. Louis, Minneapolis, New Orleans, West Superior, Indianapolis, San Francisco, Omaha." Patriotic bunting mounted above entrance. Machinery and Electricity Building visible to the northwest. Corner of Montgomery Ward Building to the north.
Interior of U.S. Government Building. "Remember the Maine" display with model of USS Maine (ACR-1).
Grand Colonnade, looking east, with Twin Tower Restaurants in background. Man stands in foreground.
Detail of Manufactures Building and Colonnade with Statue of Ceres in foreground. Potted plant at base of statue.
Remember the Maine. Signage reads: "U.S. Versus Spain. Havana and the Maine. A Realistic Production on Real Water. Admission 10 Cents." A few spectators walk by. Haunted Swing to the east.
Nebraska State Building. Trees, concession stand, and light crowd in front.
Pottawattamie County Wigwam. A pair of men walking in foreground. Star Tobacco Building and light crowd to the north.
Giant See-Saw and Power House Building.
Aerial view of Grand Court, looking west. Crowd walking around lagoon.
East Midway, looking north, with view of The Olympia, Moorish Palace and Village, Streets of Cairo, and Power House smokestacks to the northwest, and German Village to the northeast. Crowd walking.
North Midway, with view of Cyclorama, Chinese Village, Haunted Swing, and Remember the Maine. Crowd walking.
Close up of Wild West Show participants on horseback. Shooting the Chutes in the background.
Guards marching on Grand Plaza, in front of Band Stand. A cut out of President William McKinley's profile is mounted to the top of the bandstand.
North Midway, looking northeast toward Schlitz Pavilion and various restaurants. General Offices to the west. Crowd walking.
Nebraska State Building with light crowd on tree-lined walk.
U.S. Government Building with heavy crowd gathered. U.S. Lifesaving Service boat docked. Swan Boat and Gondolas in water. Fountain of Neptune waters turned on at low height.
Machinery and Electricity Building and Colonnade
machinery and electricity building and colonnade
Machinery and Electricity Building with Pompeian Colonnade and statues. Light crowd gathered. Flags mounted on roofline.
Illinois, Nebraska, Wisconsin, and Iowa State Buildings on Bluff Tract, looking southeast toward Horticultural Building. Montgomery Ward Building in foreground.
Dense Crowd gathered in front of U.S. Government Building for President William McKinley's Visit. Column marked with "x" indicates where McKinley stands.
U.S. Life Saving Service and Crowd
u.s. life saving service and crowd
U.S. Life Saving Service in docked life boat. Dense crowd gathered. Fine Arts Building and Southwest Colonnade.
Agriculture Building with Lagoon. Crowd gathered.

Agriculture Building , Administration Arch, Manufacturers Building, and Machinery and Electricity Building to the northeast, Twin Tower Restaurants to the east, and corner of Fine Arts Building visible in foreground to the south. Dense crowd gathered along lagoon.
Dense crowd gathered in front of Fine Arts Building.
View of Mines and Mining Building looking southeast across lagoon. Light crowd walking.
View of Administration Arch looking north, across lagoon. Agriculture Building to the west and Manufacturers Building to the east. Balustraded island to the west. Dense crowd gathered.
Dense crowd gathered in front of Manufacturers Building.
View of U.S. Government Building from across lagoon, looking west. Fine Arts Building to the south, and Agriculture Building to the north. Balustraded Island in foreground.
View of Liberal Arts Building looking south east across the lagoon. Balustraded Island in the foreground.
President William McKinley and Gurdon W. Wattles
president william mckinley and gurdon w. wattles
President William McKinley and Gurdon W. Wattles walking in front of dense crowd on the Grand Plaza.

Grand Court and lagoon, looking west. Mines and Mining, Liberal Arts, and Fine Arts Buildings to the south, U.S. Government Building to the west, and Agriculture Building, Administration Arch, Manufacturers Building, and Machinery and Electricity Building to the North. Light crowd. Swan boat and gondolas in lagoon.
President's Day notables walking in front of crowd gathered in front of Grand Plaza Band Stand. Profile of President William McKinley mounted on Band Stand.
Grand Colonnade with Twin Tower Restaurants visible. Gardens at east end of lagoon, with seated fairgoers.
View of Machinery and Electricity Building with lagoon. Crowd gathered. Swan Boat docked next to east end gardens.
